        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &quot;Pre-Matric Scholarship for the Students of Socially and Educationally Backward Class&quot; by the Social Justice and Empowerment Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to provide financial assistance to promote education among socially and educationally backwards students.\nThrough this scheme, scholarships per annum are provided to boys and girls studying in Standards 1 to 10 in government and aided schools. The scheme is implemented by the Director, Developing Caste Welfare, Gandhinagar, Gujarat.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "\n1. **For Boys (Std. 1 to 8):** ₹750/- scholarship.1. **For Boys (Std. 9 to 10):** ₹1000/- scholarship.1. **For Girls (Std. 1 to 5):** ₹500/- scholarship.1. **For Girls (Std. 6 to 10):** ₹1000/- scholarship.\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme aims to provide financial aid to promote education. Scholarships are provided to eligible students of Standards 1 to 10.",
