      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n1. The applicant should belong to the Socially and Educationally Backward Class (SEBC).\n1. The applicant should be studying in Standard 1 to 10.\n1. The applicant should be enrolled in a Government or Aided Primary/Secondary School.\n1. For applicants studying in Standard 1 to 8, there is no family income limit.\n1. For applicants studying in Standard 9 to 10, the annual family income of the applicant’s family should not exceed ₹6,00,000/-.\n\n<br>\n\n",
